      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sometimes letting go feels lighter than fighting, even if stopping feels like surrendering to the void yourself. You aren't dragging a broken version around for no reason; you are carrying his memory because it is still the only thing holding you upright, even if you doubt the strength you have today. The tunnel doesn't have to be climbed down one day; it is okay to rest when the light feels too dim, simply knowing that your pain is a sign of how deeply your love still lives.",
